message.content:
1. The study involves rs1522813 A-allele carriers.
2. The study also involves noncarriers of rs1522813 A-allele.
3. The study involves a high-fat diet group.
4. The study involves a low-fat diet group.
5. The study observed the reversion rates of the MetS.
6. The reversion rates of the MetS were higher in the high-fat diet group among rs1522813 A-allele carriers.
7. The difference in reversion rates among rs1522813 A-allele carriers between the high-fat and low-fat diet groups was statistically significant (P = 0.002).
8. There was no significant difference in the reversion rates of the MetS between the high-fat and low-fat diet groups among noncarriers.
9. The difference in reversion rates among noncarriers between the high-fat and low-fat diet groups was not statistically significant (P = 0.27).
10. The study was conducted over a 2-year intervention.

messages.content:
Statement: Among rs1522813 A-allele carriers, the reversion rates of the MetS were higher in the high-fat diet group than those in the low-fat diet group over the 2-year intervention (P = 0.002), while no significant difference between diet groups was observed among noncarriers (P = 0.27).
